text: There are nine St. Catherines: *Saint Caterina Volpicelli (1839-1894) *Saint Catherine of Alexandria (4th century) *Saint Catherine of Bologna (1413–1463) *Saint Catherine of Genoa (circa 1447–1510) *Saint Catherine Laboure (1806–1876) *Saint Catherine of Ricci, O.P. (1522–1590) *Saint Catherine of Siena, O.P. (Doctor of the Church, 1347–1380) *Saint Catherine of Sweden (circa 1332–1381) *Saint Katharine Drexel (1858-1955) There is a *St Catherine, Somerset *Saint Catherine's Monastery, Mount Sinai *Saint Catherine Parish, Jamaica See also: * Sainte-Catherine * Santa Caterina
title: St. Catherine
